Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of four (4) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by two (2) years extended supervision.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarcaration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.
The defendant has credit of 228 days on this case.  
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
2) Obtain his GED or HSED;
3) Have no contact with any known drug dealers or users;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.

NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, felony bail jumping.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2, 3, 4 and 5.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Pay court costs;
3) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Obtain a GED, HSED or high school diploma.
